# Vagrant VMs Project Structure

This workspace contains multiple Vagrant VM configurations for different purposes:

## VM Configurations

### Basic VMs
- [ubuntu/Vagrantfile](mdc:ubuntu/Vagrantfile) - Ubuntu Jammy 22.04 LTS with basic networking
- [centos/Vagrantfile](mdc:centos/Vagrantfile) - CentOS Stream 9 with Apache and basic provisioning

### Application VMs
- [wordpress/Vagrantfile](mdc:wordpress/Vagrantfile) - Ubuntu Focal 20.04 LTS configured for WordPress (1.6GB RAM)
- [finance/Vagrantfile](mdc:finance/Vagrantfile) - CentOS Stream 9 with finance website deployment

### Infrastructure as Code (IAC) VMs
- [wordpressIAC/Vagrantfile](mdc:wordpressIAC/Vagrantfile) - Complete WordPress stack with Apache, MySQL, PHP
- [financeIAC/Vagrantfile](mdc:financeIAC/Vagrantfile) - Finance website with automated deployment

## Network Configuration
All VMs use:
- Private network with specific IPs (192.168.56.x range)
- Public network bridged to "Realtek PCIe GbE Family Controller"
- No port forwarding configured by default

## Common Patterns
- Ubuntu VMs use `ubuntu/focal64` or `ubuntu/jammy64` boxes
- CentOS VMs use `eurolinux-vagrant/centos-stream-9` box
- All VMs have shell provisioning scripts for automated setup
